FILES
Two files used to specify local airspace and the locations of turn points. These files can be specified using
the two SettingsFiles menu items.
Airspace File
XCSoar supports airspace files using a sub set of the widely distributed OpenAir format. Files are available
from the Special Use Airspace section of the Soaring Server.
http://acro.harvard.edu/SOARING/JL/SUA
Terrain File
XCSoar uses specially formatted terrain files to determine terrain proximity. These files are available from
the XCSoar website.
Waypoints File
XCSoar uses turnpoint files written in the format designed by Cambridge Aero Instruments. Files are
available from the Soaring Turnpoints section of the Soaring Server.
http://acro.harvard.edu/SOARING/JL/TP

