POLAR SET-UP

FIGURE 18 POLAR SETUP DAILOG BOX.
The Polar Set-up dialog is used to specify the performance model of the glider used in all calculations. The
polar of the glider is set using 3 pairs of entry fields. Each set of fields is used to specify a pair of speed /
LD points. The speeds must be set in increasing order and the LD will normally be in decreasing order,
V1<V2<V3 and LD1>LD2>LD3. Best results will be produced if V1 / LD1 is the gliders best LD and
V2, V3 cover the rest of the gliders useful speed range.
It is also necessary to enter the empty weight of the glider, the weight of the pilot, and the maximum ballast
weight carried. These are entered in Kilograms
C Don't be too optimistic when entering your polar data. It is all too easy to set your LD too
high and you will rapidly see yourself undershooting on final glide
TASK MENU
Task Start Line

FIGURE 19 TASK START LINE TYPE SPECIFICATION
The Task Start Line menu item is used to specify the type of start line used. There are two options, a
line/semicircle start zone and a cylinder start zone. The radius of both types of zone can be modified.
Once the glider has entered the start zone, a start is registered as soon as the glider leaves the zone. To re-
start a task, simply change the active waypoint back to the start zone.

