DATA DISPLAY FIELDS
It is possible to display one of many different parameters in each of the displayed information fields. Each
displayed information field can also display two possible values, one in cruise flight and a different one in
climbing flight. For example a field might display distance to the next waypoint in cruising flight and the
height gain during thermal flight.
TO CHANGE A DATA DISPLAY FIELD




FIGURE 23 CHANGING A DATA DISPLAY FIELD
1. Ensure that the FileLock menu item is unchecked.
2. Select the data display field you wish to change.
3. Select a new pair of items from the list of possible data items.
4. Select OK to confirm.
5. Ensure that the FileLock menu item is re- checked.
