Detailed descriptions of the various fields are given below.
ALTITUDE GPS - ALT
This is the height above mean sea level reported by the GPS.
ALTITUDE AGL ­ A.G.L.
This is the GPS altitude minus the terrain height obtained from the terrain file.
AVERAGE - AVERAGE
A 30 second rolling average based of the reported GPS altitude.
BEARING - BEARING
True bearing of the next waypoint.
CURRENT L/D ­ L/D
The instantaneous ground speed divided by vertical speed.
CRUISE L/D ­ CR L/D
The distance from the top of the last thermal, divided by the altitude lost since the top of the last thermal.
GROUND SPEED - SPEED
Ground speed measured by the GPS.
LAST THERMAL AVERAGE - LA
Total altitude gain/loss in the last thermal divided by the time spent circling.
LAST THERMAL GAIN - LG
Total altitude gain/loss in the last thermal.
LAST THERMAL TIME - LT
Time spent circling in the last thermal.
MCREADY SETTING ­ MCREADY
The current McReady setting. Also used to adjust the McReady Setting.

